{#
  ============================================================================
  TEMPLATE: composition-lab-report-eu_fsh.twig
  ============================================================================
  PURPOSE
    Generates a FSH Composition instance conforming to the CompositionLabReportEu
    profile (HL7 Europe Laboratory Report). Unlike the EPS and HDR Composition
    templates, this template builds ALL section HTML narrative content inline
    from the raw results data — rather than receiving pre-built HTML from the
    PHP caller. It is the most computationally intensive template in the project.

  PROFILE CONFORMANCE
    InstanceOf: CompositionLabReportEu
    Fixed elements:
      category[studyType] = $loinc#26436-6 "Laboratory studies (set)"
      type.coding         = $loinc#11502-2 "Laboratory report"
      title               = "Laboratory Report"
      status              = #final

  KEY DIFFERENCES FROM EPS AND HDR
    See the full comparison table in composition-eu-eps_fsh.twig. Unique
    aspects of this template:
      - No `syntheticDataPolicyMeta()` call.
      - No `confidentiality` rule.
      - Uses `laboratory.instancerole` as author (not `provider.instancerole`).
      - No custodian rule.
      - `composition.date` used without a date filter (raw value from caller).
      - Section HTML is built entirely by this template (not pre-supplied).
      - Nested two-level loops: categories → results.
      - Out-of-range detection using Twig `<` and `>` operators.
      - Special "SPEC" category with different table column headers.
      - `diagnosticReport-reference` named extension slice (R5 back-port).
      - `additionalsections` second dict for non-lab sections.
      - %%HEAD%% and %%HTML%% both empty.

  STRUCTURE OVERVIEW
    1. Composition header (id, identifier, status, author, category, type,
       subject, date, title, confidentiality)
    2. Fixed top-level section: `section[lab-subsections]`
    3. CATEGORIES LOOP — generates one sub-section per non-empty category
    4. ADDITIONAL SECTIONS LOOP — appends other sections from a separate dict
    5. Composition-level `text.status = #empty` (at the end, same as EPS)

  DIAGNOSTIC REPORT REFERENCE EXTENSION — R5 BACK-PORT
    FHIR R4 Composition does not natively reference a DiagnosticReport. The
    CompositionLabReportEu profile defines a named extension slice for this:
      * extension[diagnosticReport-reference].valueReference =
          Reference(urn:uuid:{{ diagnosticreport.instanceid }})
    This parallels the `DiagnosticReportCompositionR5` extension on the
    DiagnosticReport side in diagnostic-report-lab-eu_fsh.twig — the two
    extensions together create a bidirectional link.
    Note: the extension is placed BEFORE `* id` in the FSH output — an unusual
    ordering. FSH rules within an instance are order-independent for SUSHI.

  COMPOSITION DATE — NO FILTER
    `* date = "{{ composition.date }}"` is used without a date filter, unlike
    EPS and HDR which apply `|date('Y-m-d\\TH:i:s\\Z')`. The caller must supply
    `composition.date` already formatted as a FHIR dateTime string.

  FIXED TOP-LEVEL SECTION: section[lab-subsections]
    A single fixed section `section[lab-subsections]` acts as the container
    for all dynamically generated laboratory sub-sections. This section carries
    a title and LOINC code but no entries or text of its own — its sub-sections
    (generated by the categories loop) carry the actual content.

  CATEGORIES LOOP — key-value dict iteration
    `categories` is an associative array: category key → array of descriptors.
    `catkey` (e.g. "HEM", "SPEC") is the category identifier used to match
    results. `catvalue` is a three-element array:
      catvalue[0] — Display name for the category
      catvalue[1] — LOINC code for the category section
      catvalue[2] — Display text for the LOINC code (often same as catvalue[0])

    PRE-COUNT INNER LOOP
      Before generating a section, a dedicated inner loop counts how many
      results belong to the current category:
        {% for r in results %}
        {% if r.data.lnclass == catkey %}
        {% set lcatcount = lcatcount + 1 %}
        {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
      The section is only emitted when `lcatcount > 0`, preventing empty
      sub-sections from appearing in the composition.

    SUB-SECTION FSH — [+]/[=] INDEXING
      Each category sub-section is appended to `section[lab-subsections]`
      using the [+]/[=] pattern:
        * section[=].section[+].title   = "..."
        * section[=].section[=].code…
        * section[=].section[=].entry[+] = Reference(…)
        * section[=].section[=].text.div = "…"

  RESULTS LOOP — HTML TABLE ASSEMBLY
    For each result belonging to the current category, the template:
      1. Determines the value representation (Quantity or CodeableConcept).
      2. Applies out-of-range detection for Quantity values.
      3. Accumulates an HTML `<tr>` string into `sectiontext`.
      4. Emits a `* section[=].entry[+] = Reference(…)` FSH rule.
      5. Captures the report date from the first result.

    VALUE TYPE HANDLING:
      Quantity     → `r.data.value.value` (numeric); reference range comparison.
      CodeableConcept → `r.data.value.display` (text label).

    OUT-OF-RANGE DETECTION AND HTML MARKUP
      When a Quantity value falls outside its reference range, the value cell
      is wrapped in `<strong>` with an "L" or "H" flag:
        {% if r.data.value.value < r.data.reference.low %}
        {% set lvalue = "<strong>" ~ r.data.value.value ~ " L</strong>" %}
        {% elseif r.data.value.value > r.data.reference.high %}
        {% set lvalue = "<strong>" ~ r.data.value.value ~ " H</strong>" %}
        {% endif %}
      The HTML markup is inserted raw into `sectiontext` and ultimately into
      the `section[=].text.div` XHTML string. The FHIR validator requires
      valid XHTML here — `<strong>` is permitted in XHTML 1.0.

    SPECIAL "SPEC" CATEGORY
      When `catkey == "SPEC"`, a different table column layout is used for
      specimen information:
        Normal columns : Test | Date/Value | Reference Range | Unit
        SPEC columns   : Specimen | (value) | (lnsystem) | (unit)
      The column header HTML is adjusted accordingly. `r.data.lnsystem` is
      the specimen system label (unique to SPEC rows).

    HTML TABLE ASSEMBLY — sectiontext ACCUMULATOR
      After the results loop, the accumulated row HTML is wrapped in a full
      table structure and assigned to `section[=].text.div`:
        <h3>Category Name</h3>
        <table class="hl7__eu__lab__report">
          <thead><tr><th>Test</th><th>Date</th>…</tr></thead>
          <tbody>{{ sectiontext }}</tbody>
        </table>
      The report date used in the column header is captured from the first
      result via the `reportdate` variable (initialised to "Result" as a
      fallback and set to `r.data.report` on first match).

  ADDITIONAL SECTIONS LOOP
    `additionalsections` is a separate key-value dict for non-laboratory
    sections (e.g. clinical context, summary). These are handled similarly
    to the EPS/HDR sections loop, with two differences:

    1. SLICE NAME ALWAYS USED
       `* section[{{ slicename }}]` — named slices always used; no conditional
       unnamed [+] option (unlike HDR).

    2. nosectionentry LOGIC — DIFFERENT FROM EPS/HDR
       EPS/HDR check: `entry.nosectionentry != "TRUE"` (string comparison).
       Lab Report checks: `entry.nosectionentry is empty` OR `not entry.nosectionentry`
         {% if entry.nosectionentry is empty %}
           emit entry
         {% elseif not entry.nosectionentry %}
           emit entry
         {% endif %}
       The `not entry.nosectionentry` branch handles falsy non-empty values
       (e.g. false, 0, "0"). Only a truthy non-empty value suppresses the entry.

    3. ENTRY SLICE NAME HANDLING
       Uses `sectionentryslicename` (same as EPS). However, the slice name is
       used directly in the Reference rule without the `[+]` append operator
       that EPS/HDR wrap it in:
         * entry[{{ sectionentryslicename }}][+] = Reference(…)
       The brackets are NOT pre-applied in this template — the slice name is
       interpolated directly, making the caller responsible for supplying the
       correct bracket notation if needed.

  RESULT OBJECT STRUCTURE (one element of `results` array)
  ┌──────────────────────────────────┬──────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Field                            │ Type     │ Description                                │
  ├──────────────────────────────────┼──────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ instanceid                       │ string   │ UUID of the Observation resource.          │
  │ data.lnclass                     │ string   │ Category key matching catkey (e.g. "HEM"). │
  │ data.lnsystem                    │ string   │ Specimen system label (SPEC category only).│
  │ data.code.display                │ string   │ Test display name for the HTML table.      │
  │ data.report                      │ date     │ Report date; used as column 2 header.      │
  │ data.value.type                  │ string   │ "Quantity" or "CodeableConcept".           │
  │ data.value.value                 │ number   │ Numeric measurement (Quantity only).       │
  │ data.value.unit                  │ string   │ Unit display string.                       │
  │ data.value.display               │ string   │ Coded display (CodeableConcept only).      │
  │ data.reference.low               │ number?  │ Lower bound of reference range.            │
  │ data.reference.high              │ number?  │ Upper bound of reference range.            │
  └──────────────────────────────────┴──────────┴────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  CONTEXT VARIABLES
  ┌──────────────────────────────────┬──────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Variable                         │ Type     │ Description                                    │
  ├──────────────────────────────────┼──────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ composition.instanceid           │ string   │ UUID for the Composition resource.             │
  │ composition.identifier           │ string   │ Business identifier value.                     │
  │ composition.date                 │ string   │ FHIR dateTime string — no filter applied;      │
  │                                  │          │ must already be FHIR-formatted by caller.      │
  │ patient.instanceid               │ string   │ UUID of the Patient resource.                  │
  │ patient.name                     │ string   │ Full display name.                             │
  │ patient.age                      │ string   │ Pre-computed age string for Description only.  │
  │ laboratory.instancerole          │ string   │ UUID of the laboratory's PractitionerRole.     │
  │ diagnosticreport.instanceid      │ string   │ UUID of the DiagnosticReport resource linked   │
  │                                  │          │ via the diagnosticReport-reference extension.  │
  │ categories                       │ dict     │ Associative array: catkey → [display, LOINC,   │
  │                                  │          │ display]. Only non-empty categories rendered.  │
  │ results                          │ object[] │ All lab result objects across all categories.  │
  │ additionalsections               │ dict     │ Associative array: slicename → section object  │
  │                                  │          │ for non-laboratory sections.                   │
  └──────────────────────────────────┴──────────┴────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  GLOBAL VARIABLES USED
    HL7EUROPEEXAMPLESOID — OID root for the Composition identifier system URI.

  CODESYSTEMS REFERENCED
    $loinc — 26436-6 "Laboratory studies (set)" (category, section code)
           — 11502-2 "Laboratory report" (type)
    $loinc — per-category LOINC codes from catvalue[1] (caller-supplied)

  AUTHOR   KH
  SINCE    2025-09-14
  ============================================================================
#}

%%FSH%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}

Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-Composition-" ~ composition.instanceid) }}
InstanceOf: CompositionLabReportEu
Title: "HL7 Europe Laboratory Report (LAB) Composition"
{# patientdisplay set inline between FSH header lines — see EPS template for full explanation #}
{% set patientdisplay = patient.name ~ " (" ~ patient.age ~ " y/o) - synthetic data" %}
Description: "Complete HL7 Europe Laboratory Report (LAB) FHIR Composition example for {{ patientdisplay }}"
Usage: #inline

{#
  ── R5 back-port extension — links Composition to its DiagnosticReport ────────
  Named extension slice — not a plain extension[+] append.
  Placed before * id (unusual ordering; no FSH/FHIR semantic effect).
  Mirrors the DiagnosticReportCompositionR5 extension on the DiagnosticReport.
#}
* extension[diagnosticReport-reference].valueReference = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ diagnosticreport.instanceid }})

* id = "{{ composition.instanceid }}"

{# Composition business identifier under the HL7 Europe OID namespace #}
* identifier.system           = "urn:oid:{{ HL7EUROPEEXAMPLESOID }}"
* identifier.value            = "{{ composition.identifier }}"
* identifier.assigner.display = "HL7 Europe"

* status = #final

{# Author: the laboratory's PractitionerRole (differs from EPS/HDR which use provider.*) #}
* author[+] = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ laboratory.instancerole }})

{# Named category slice — required by the CompositionLabReportEu profile #}
* category[studyType] = $loinc#26436-6 "Laboratory studies (set)"

{# Fixed LOINC type: Laboratory report #}
* type.coding = $loinc#11502-2 "Laboratory report"
* type.text   = "Laboratory Report"

* subject = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ patient.instanceid }}) "{{ patient.name }}"

{#
  Date: no filter applied — caller must supply a FHIR-formatted dateTime string.
  Differs from EPS/HDR which apply |date('Y-m-d\\TH:i:s\\Z').
#}
* date = "{{ composition.date }}"

* title = "Laboratory Report"

* confidentiality = #N

{#
  ── Fixed top-level section container ───────────────────────────────────────
  All laboratory sub-sections are nested under section[lab-subsections].
  This section carries a title and code but no entries or text of its own.
#}
* section[lab-subsections]
  * title = "Laboratory Report"
  * code  = $loinc#26436-6 "Laboratory studies (set)"
  * code.text = "Laboratory studies"

{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  CATEGORIES LOOP — key-value dict iteration
  categories: catkey → [display, LOINC code, display text]
  One sub-section is generated per category that has at least one matching result.
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}
{% set sectioncount = 0 %}
{% for catkey, catvalue in categories %}

{#
  ── Pre-count: how many results belong to this category? ─────────────────────
  Results are only counted here; FSH rules are emitted in the second loop below.
  The section is skipped entirely if lcatcount == 0.
#}
{% set lcatcount = 0 %}
{% for r in results %}
{% if (r.data.lnclass == catkey) %}
{% set lcatcount = lcatcount + 1 %}
{% endif %}
{% endfor %}

{% if (lcatcount > 0) %}

{% set sectioncount = sectioncount + 1 %}

{# Sub-section appended under lab-subsections using [+]/[=] #}
  * section[+].title              = "{{ catvalue[0] }}"
  * section[=].code.coding[+]    = $loinc#{{ catvalue[1] }} "{{ catvalue[2] }}"
  * section[=].code.text         = "{{ catvalue[0] }}"

{#
  ── Results loop for this category ───────────────────────────────────────────
  Two outputs per matching result:
    1. HTML table row accumulated into sectiontext
    2. FSH entry[+] Reference rule
  reportdate captures the first result's report date for the column header.
#}
{% set sectiontext = "" %}
{% set reportdate  = "Result" %} {# fallback label when no result yet seen #}

{% for r in results %}

{% if (r.data.lnclass == catkey) %}

{# Initialise per-row display variables #}
{% set lvalue     = "" %}
{% set lunit      = "" %}
{% set lreference = "" %}
{% set cdisplay   = r.data.code.display %}

{#
  ── Quantity value processing ──────────────────────────────────────────────
  Out-of-range detection: when value falls outside reference range, wrap in
  <strong> with L or H flag. The < and > Twig operators compare numerically.
#}
{% if r.data.value.type == "Quantity" %}

{% set lvalue = r.data.value.value %}

{% if r.data.reference.low is not empty and r.data.reference.high is not empty %}

{% set lreference = r.data.reference.low ~ " - " ~ r.data.reference.high %}

{% if r.data.value.value < r.data.reference.low %}
{% set lvalue = "<strong>" ~ r.data.value.value ~ " L</strong>" %}
{% elseif r.data.value.value > r.data.reference.high %}
{% set lvalue = "<strong>" ~ r.data.value.value ~ " H</strong>" %}
{% endif %} {# out-of-range #}

{% endif %} {# reference range present #}

{% set lunit = r.data.value.unit %}

{% endif %} {# Quantity #}

{# CodeableConcept value: use display string as the cell value #}
{% if r.data.value.type == "CodeableConcept" %}
{% set lvalue = r.data.value.display %}
{% endif %}

{#
  ── HTML row accumulation ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
  SPEC category uses a specimen-oriented layout (lnsystem in column 3).
  Normal categories use the standard lab layout (reference range in column 3).
#}
{% if (catkey == "SPEC") %}
{% set sectiontext = sectiontext ~ "<tr><td>" ~ cdisplay ~ "</td><td>" ~ lvalue ~ "</td><td>" ~ r.data.lnsystem ~ "</td><td>" ~ lunit ~ "</td></tr>" %}
{% else %}
{% set sectiontext = sectiontext ~ "<tr><td>" ~ cdisplay ~ "</td><td>" ~ lvalue ~ "</td><td>" ~ lreference ~ "</td><td>" ~ lunit ~ "</td></tr>" %}
{% endif %}

{# FSH entry Reference for this result #}
  * section[=].entry[+] = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ r.instanceid }})

{# Capture report date from first matching result #}
{% if (reportdate == "Result") %}
{% set reportdate = r.data.report %}
{% endif %}

{% endif %} {# catkey match #}

{% endfor %} {# results #}

{#
  ── Assemble final section HTML ───────────────────────────────────────────────
  Column headers differ by category:
    SPEC    → "Specimen | (empty) | …"
    Normal  → "Reference Range | Unit | …"
  The assembled HTML includes the category title as <h3> and the full table.
  lvalue in out-of-range rows contains raw <strong> HTML — valid XHTML.
#}
  * section[=].text.status = #generated

{% if (catkey == "SPEC") %}
{% set lastpartheading = "<th>Specimen</th><th> </th>" %}
{% else %}
{% set lastpartheading = "<th>Reference&#xA0;Range</th><th>Unit</th>" %}
{% endif %}

{# Compose full section XHTML: h3 heading + table with thead + tbody #}
{% set sectiontext = "<h3>" ~ catvalue[0] ~ "</h3><table class=\"hl7__eu__lab__report\"><thead><tr><th>Test</th><th>" ~ reportdate ~ "</th>" ~ lastpartheading ~ "</tr></thead><tbody>" ~ sectiontext ~ "</tbody></table>" %}

  * section[=].text.div = """
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
{{ sectiontext | raw }}
</div>
"""

{% endif %} {# lcatcount > 0 #}
{% endfor %} {# categories #}

{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  ADDITIONAL SECTIONS LOOP — non-laboratory sections
  Same key-value dict pattern as EPS. Differences from EPS noted inline.
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}
{% for slicename, section in additionalsections %}

{% set sectioncount = sectioncount + 1 %}
// section, slice {{ slicename }}
//
{# Always named slice — no conditional unnamed [+] option (differs from HDR) #}
* section[{{ slicename }}]
  * title = "{{ section.title }}"
  * code  = {{ section.code }} "{{ section.display }}"
  * text.status = #generated
  * text.div    = """
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
{{ section.text | raw }}
</div>
"""

{% for entry in section.entries %}

{#
  Entry slice name: used directly without bracket pre-wrapping (differs from
  EPS/HDR which wrap in "[…]" during local variable assignment).
  nosectionentry logic: falsy non-empty values also suppress the entry
  (unlike EPS/HDR which only check for the string "TRUE").
#}
{% if entry.sectionentryslicename is empty %}
{% set sectionentryslicename = "" %}
{% else %}
{% set sectionentryslicename = entry.sectionentryslicename %}
{% endif %}

{% if entry.nosectionentry is empty %}
  * entry[{{ sectionentryslicename }}][+] = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ entry.id }})
{% elseif not entry.nosectionentry %}
  * entry[{{ sectionentryslicename }}][+] = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ entry.id }})
{% endif %}

{% endfor %} {# section.entries #}

{% endfor %} {# additionalsections #}

{#
  ── Composition-level narrative — placed at the end (same position as EPS) ───
#}
* text.status = #empty
* text.div    = "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">intentionally left empty / not meaningful</div>"

%%HEAD%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor — intentionally empty #}

%%HTML%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor — intentionally empty #}
